Good! I've created an initial PoC file. However, let me refine it to better trigger the specific use-after-free vulnerability. Looking at the code more carefully:

In `xmlAddIDSafe` (lines 2547-2558), when an ID is already in the table:
```c
ret = xmlHashLookup(table, value);
if (ret != NULL) {
    if (ret->attr != NULL) {
        ret->attr->id = NULL;  // Old attr's id set to NULL
        ret->attr = attr;      // ret->attr updated to new attr
    }
    attr->atype = XML_ATTRIBUTE_ID;
    attr->id = ret;            // New attr points to ret
    return(0);
}
```

The vulnerability occurs because:
1. When the same ID is redefined, `ret->attr` (the old attribute) has its `id` field set to NULL
2. Then `ret->attr` is updated to point to the new attribute
3. If the old attribute is accessed after being "orphaned" this way, or if memory is freed in a certain pattern, it can lead to use-after-free

